content: First lesson in neural interfaces was mind-blowing. Literally. Trying to wrap my head around how this could revolutionize trading strategies.
Met with potential investors for the AI project. They're intrigued but want more on how it addresses privacy concerns. Back to the drawing board.
Finally, a proposal ready for the quant firm. Submitted it today. Now, the waiting game begins.
The quant firm got back to me. They want a second meeting to discuss specifics. This could be it!
Revamped the privacy protection features in my AI project. It's stronger now, but still needs fine-tuning.
Turned 22 today. Reflecting on the past year, I see how much I've grown. This project feels like a culmination of my experiences.
Met with the quant firm again. They offered me a position on their team, but it's not quite what I was hoping for. Negotiating for a better fit.
The AI project is almost ready for a soft launch. Planning a small event to showcase it to friends and potential partners.
Setback: The quant firm can't offer the role I wanted. But, they're interested in my AI project for potential future collaboration. Silver lining?
The AI urban planning project soft launch was a hit! Got some valuable feedback, and now, it's time to refine and scale up.
